Bit Manipulation means operating at the level of individual bits using:

AND (&), OR (|), XOR (^), NOT (~), Shift (<<, >>)

Very fast, low-level operations.

Useful for optimization, number theory, encryption.

Example:

java
Copy code
int a = 5; // 101
int b = 3; // 011
System.out.println(a & b); // Output: 1 (001)
System.out.println(a | b); // Output: 7 (111)
